WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:03.335
        Jeannie.

00:05.506 --> 00:07.339
Jeannie, uh,
would you come out, please?

00:07.375 --> 00:09.174
I'd like my breakfast.

00:13.381 --> 00:16.248
          Yes, master, one egg
        and two slices of bacon.

00:16.283 --> 00:17.249
That's right.

00:17.284 --> 00:19.851
                    [SIGHS]

00:19.887 --> 00:21.220
What's the matter?

00:21.255 --> 00:23.389
                 Oh...nothing.

00:23.424 --> 00:25.457
Oh, now, now, come on.
Something's on your mind.

00:25.493 --> 00:26.858
W-what is it?

00:26.894 --> 00:29.094
                      Well...

00:29.130 --> 00:32.131
               If you must know,
              I am being wasted.
    Huh?

00:32.165 --> 00:35.234
     Anyone can make you one egg
       and two slices of bacon.

00:35.269 --> 00:36.935
                Oh, if you would
                 only permit me,

00:36.970 --> 00:38.937
      I could do such big things
               for you.

00:38.972 --> 00:41.040
        I could give you castles
             and gold and--

00:41.075 --> 00:43.242
One egg, two slices of bacon,
not too crisp, please.

00:43.277 --> 00:45.677
           I gave my last master
             a fleet of ships.

00:45.712 --> 00:46.878
And a cup of coffee.

00:46.914 --> 00:49.281
           Why do you not let me
                 help you?

00:49.316 --> 00:53.185
Jeannie, I-- I really don't
need a fleet of ships.

00:53.220 --> 00:55.454
But if I do, believe me,
you'll be the first to know.

00:55.489 --> 00:57.689
    Perhaps a villa on the Nile?

00:57.724 --> 00:59.425
Really, I'm very happy
with the house.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.993
It's-- It's very comfortable.
Just breakfast, please.

01:02.029 --> 01:04.328
    Major Healey loved the yacht
             I gave him.

01:04.364 --> 01:06.532
Yeah. Look at the trouble
      he got into.

01:09.470 --> 01:11.303
There is a wonderful
diamond mine in Africa

01:11.338 --> 01:12.371
I could get you.

01:12.406 --> 01:14.172
            Jeannie, I--
    I don't need a diamond mine.

01:14.208 --> 01:15.773
                I get a salary
             from the air force,

01:15.809 --> 01:17.209
                  very adequate.
                     And, uh--

01:17.244 --> 01:19.244
                And I must say,
               I <i> earn</i> my salary.

01:19.279 --> 01:20.312
          See, that's the point.

01:20.347 --> 01:21.679
             I like to do things
                 for myself.

01:21.715 --> 01:23.681
I will be a laughing stock.

01:23.717 --> 01:26.485
  A genie who can only bring
  her master bacon and eggs.

01:26.520 --> 01:28.553
   Well, look at it this way:
         who's to know?

01:28.589 --> 01:33.324
Master, wish for one big thing.

01:33.360 --> 01:35.059
     Jeannie, I don't need
         anything. I--

01:35.095 --> 01:36.428
    Oh, it would make me
         so happy.

01:36.463 --> 01:38.062
           You do not
   even have to say it aloud.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.564
       Just think it.

01:39.600 --> 01:41.767
   But I don't want anything.
            Really.

01:41.802 --> 01:42.834
            Please?

01:44.405 --> 01:47.739
Come on, now, the biggest thing
       you can think of.

01:47.775 --> 01:49.407
                      Uh--
    Ready?

01:49.443 --> 01:50.576
                     Yeah.

01:51.579 --> 01:52.644
      [ELEPHANT TRUMPETS]

01:52.680 --> 01:55.146
What are you going
 to do with that?

01:55.182 --> 01:57.049
                  Yeah...

01:57.084 --> 01:59.384
        It was the biggest thing
            I could think of.

02:01.154 --> 02:02.354
         Major Nelson?

02:02.389 --> 02:04.323
          It's Doctor Bellows.
        Get out of here, please?

02:04.358 --> 02:05.457
          And take him with you.

02:05.492 --> 02:07.158
      I will leave.
You may keep the elephant.

02:07.194 --> 02:08.594
                 But wait--

02:11.265 --> 02:12.231
                    Uh--

02:12.266 --> 02:13.665
Oh, there you are,
  Major Nelson.

02:15.669 --> 02:16.901
                 Hi, there.

02:22.476 --> 02:25.110
             [♪♪♪]

03:08.689 --> 03:11.290
             [♪♪♪]

03:16.029 --> 03:18.863
      [ELEPHANT TRUMPETS]

03:22.403 --> 03:24.403
    I can't <i> wait... </i>
to hear your explanation

03:24.438 --> 03:26.237
of what you're doing
  with an elephant

03:26.273 --> 03:27.339
    in your bedroom.

03:27.374 --> 03:29.140
          Uh, I'm glad
      you asked that, sir.

03:29.176 --> 03:30.842
      Uh, a friend of mine
         left him here?

03:30.877 --> 03:33.912
    Uh, and my next question
        is going to be:

03:33.947 --> 03:35.380
              why?

03:35.416 --> 03:37.916
          Ye-- Well, it's a very
           valuable animal, sir.

03:37.951 --> 03:40.084
    I mean, you just can't leave
        an elephant anywhere.

03:40.120 --> 03:41.085
               [GIGGLES]

03:41.121 --> 03:42.220
      Uh, my friend takes him

03:42.255 --> 03:44.423
        on safaris uh, uh,
        in Africa with him.

03:44.458 --> 03:46.257
           He insists
   that he stay indoors, sir.

03:46.293 --> 03:48.026
       You know how it is
         with animals.

03:48.061 --> 03:51.029
   Major, I want you to wait
          right here.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.731
Do you understand?

03:52.766 --> 03:54.533
          Right here.

04:07.848 --> 04:09.547
                Jeannie.

04:09.583 --> 04:11.016
              Very funny.

04:11.051 --> 04:12.084
                Jeannie.

04:13.353 --> 04:14.853
          Oh, are you satisfied?

04:14.888 --> 04:16.755
Well, it was you who wished
     for the elephant.

04:16.790 --> 04:18.724
      Would you mind getting rid
                of him?

04:18.759 --> 04:20.524
    If you wish.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.195
                What's this?

04:23.230 --> 04:24.763
       [LAUGHS]
I did not know, master.

04:24.798 --> 04:26.464
Were you thinking
 about a poodle?

04:26.499 --> 04:28.700
            Yeah, I guess I was.

04:28.735 --> 04:30.134
       When I was a kid,

04:30.170 --> 04:32.504
     I had a little poodle
         called Tiger.

04:33.440 --> 04:34.839
       Hi, there, Tiger.

04:34.874 --> 04:35.873
                     Hi, there.

04:35.909 --> 04:37.909
        [POODLE SNARLS]

04:39.446 --> 04:40.445
              Oh.

04:41.381 --> 04:43.715
  An elephant in his bedroom?

04:43.750 --> 04:46.984
       General Peterson,
   I saw it with my own eyes.

04:47.020 --> 04:49.221
       His name is Tiger.

04:49.256 --> 04:52.657
Doctor, what would
an elephant be doing

04:52.693 --> 04:54.659
in Major Nelson's bedroom?

04:54.695 --> 04:56.961
             With Major Nelson,
           anything is possible.

04:56.996 --> 04:59.030
                   I repeat,
              general, anything.

04:59.065 --> 05:01.866
 You have no idea what I've been
   going through with him, sir.

05:01.901 --> 05:07.038
  But now I think we finally got
   his psyche pinned to the mat.

05:07.073 --> 05:09.341
            He'll never talk
        his way out of this one.

05:09.376 --> 05:12.577
If this is another one
of your wild goose chases--

05:12.613 --> 05:14.812
       Wild elephant chase, sir.

05:14.848 --> 05:17.682
      We're going on the biggest
          safari of them all:

05:17.718 --> 05:20.285
           bagging Major Nelson.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.989
Oh, Doctor Bellows,
 General Peterson.

05:25.024 --> 05:26.758
        Sorry to barge in on you
            like this, Tony.

05:26.793 --> 05:28.526
 This will only take a minute,
             major.

05:28.562 --> 05:30.228
 He's in the bedroom, general.

05:35.969 --> 05:37.569
                  Under the bed?

05:37.604 --> 05:39.471
He was standing right there.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.038
    I swear he was.

05:41.074 --> 05:43.441
        This big.

05:48.582 --> 05:50.248
                       Tony.

05:50.284 --> 05:51.383
        Yes.

05:51.418 --> 05:53.585
        Did you have an elephant
            in your bedroom?

05:53.620 --> 05:56.421
[LAUGHING]
Did I have an elephant
in my bedroom?

05:56.456 --> 05:59.223
  Uh-uh, you're not gonna get
    out of this one, major.

05:59.259 --> 06:00.792
     You called him Tiger.

06:00.827 --> 06:02.627
Tiger. Tiger.

06:02.663 --> 06:05.062
Oh, oh, Tiger.

06:05.098 --> 06:07.064
              Yes.
       Now do you recall?

06:07.100 --> 06:08.800
    Yes.
Oh, yes, sir.

06:08.835 --> 06:10.868
        Here we are.

06:10.904 --> 06:11.903
 Here's Tiger.

06:11.938 --> 06:13.371
He's a cute
little fellow, huh?

06:13.407 --> 06:15.239
         That's Tiger?

06:15.275 --> 06:18.610
    So we're going on a safari
 to hunt wild elephants, are we?

06:18.645 --> 06:22.314
          Doctor, I want you
     in my office in 30 minutes.

06:22.349 --> 06:25.350
        And be prepared to spend
         the afternoon with me.

06:25.385 --> 06:26.651
           Yes, sir.

06:26.687 --> 06:28.420
              I'm sorry
     to have bothered you, Tony.

06:28.455 --> 06:30.121
Oh, that's quite
all right, sir.

06:30.156 --> 06:31.523
No bother at all.

06:31.558 --> 06:34.426
          It won't happen again.

06:34.461 --> 06:36.494
       You haven't heard
       the last of this.

06:36.530 --> 06:39.297
          You haven't heard
       the last of this, major.

06:39.333 --> 06:40.932
          Oh, general.

06:43.303 --> 06:44.469
             [SNARLING]

06:48.742 --> 06:49.907
                  Jeannie.

06:49.942 --> 06:51.976
            You see?
        I can help you.

06:52.011 --> 06:54.279
      How did I get in this spot
          in the first place?

06:54.314 --> 06:56.347
       I feel sorry
    for Doctor Bellows.

06:56.383 --> 06:57.915
    He's a very nice man.

06:57.950 --> 06:59.317
                Well, I'd feel
              sorry for him too,

06:59.352 --> 07:00.318
           except for one thing:

07:00.353 --> 07:01.619
            If he ever finds out
                 about you,

07:01.655 --> 07:03.588
        I'm gonna get thrown out
          of the space program.

07:03.623 --> 07:05.089
    Oh, could you not
     explain to him

07:05.124 --> 07:07.559
    that you found me
in a bottle on the beach?

07:07.594 --> 07:11.196
               Sure, that's--
           Of course, of course.

07:11.231 --> 07:13.198
           And when I'm finished
           explaining it to him,

07:13.233 --> 07:14.899
        he'll have me locked up.
                 Ha, ha.

07:14.934 --> 07:16.000
          [DOOR OPENS]

07:16.035 --> 07:17.034
                 They're back.

07:19.639 --> 07:20.871
                      Hi.
    Hi, Tony.

07:20.907 --> 07:22.139
                  It's only you.

07:22.175 --> 07:25.577
Boy, you sure know how to make
    a fellow feel welcome.

07:25.612 --> 07:26.944
     Hello, Captain Healey.

07:26.979 --> 07:28.979
          Hi, Jeannie.
         How's tricks?

07:29.015 --> 07:30.014
           [CHUCKLES]

07:30.049 --> 07:31.148
                 [CHUCKLES]

07:31.184 --> 07:33.585
I have not had much time
   to practice them.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.553
Well, you should've picked me
      for your master.

07:35.589 --> 07:37.121
    I'd keep you working
      24 hours a day.

07:37.156 --> 07:39.056
 Oh, I am very pleased
with the master I have.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.191
    Thank you.

07:40.226 --> 07:41.859
Well, if you should change
your mind,

07:41.894 --> 07:44.062
 remember I, uh, pay overtime.

07:44.097 --> 07:45.630
       Hey, what's that?

07:45.665 --> 07:46.698
               That's Tiger.

07:46.733 --> 07:48.199
         Hi, Tiger.

07:48.234 --> 07:49.467
            [SNARLS]

07:52.005 --> 07:55.406
Uh, didn't I see Doctor Bellows
and General Peterson leave here?

07:55.441 --> 07:56.407
                Yeah, yeah.

07:56.442 --> 07:58.042
               Doctor Bellows
            is seeing elephants.

07:58.077 --> 07:59.911
         Well, that's
 the psychiatry game for ya.

07:59.946 --> 08:01.312
Well, we better be
moving along.

08:01.347 --> 08:03.614
They're running some films
of yours on your space walk

08:03.650 --> 08:05.817
      and some big brass
is coming down from Washington,

08:05.852 --> 08:07.318
    and, uh, they'd like us
          to be there.

08:07.353 --> 08:08.352
                Yeah, okay.

08:08.388 --> 08:09.954
    Um, I'll be home for dinner.

08:09.990 --> 08:11.622
 I shall fix something special,
            master.

08:11.658 --> 08:13.691
   When you're through,
maybe you could mix me, uh,

08:13.726 --> 08:16.094
     up a little something.
A little-- Maybe hors d'oeuvres.

08:16.129 --> 08:18.763
            [LAUGHS]

08:18.799 --> 08:21.332
   And what do you wish for,
         little Tiger?

08:25.605 --> 08:27.638
             There you go.

08:29.276 --> 08:31.409
                    [LAUGHS]

08:31.444 --> 08:32.943
                      Mmm.

08:38.484 --> 08:41.953
           PETERSON:
   There's Major Nelson ready
    to step off into space.

08:41.988 --> 08:43.855
         There he goes.

08:43.890 --> 08:46.291
           Major Healey,
   when you were at the controls

08:46.326 --> 08:47.992
 and Major Nelson left the ship,

08:48.028 --> 08:50.962
 did you notice any difference
in the handling of the controls?

08:50.997 --> 08:53.230
Well, when he stepped out,
the ship yawed a bit,

08:53.266 --> 08:54.799
but it was easy to correct.

08:54.834 --> 08:57.935
              MAN:
   Major Nelson, did you have
          any problem

08:57.971 --> 08:59.236
 adjusting to floating in space

08:59.272 --> 09:02.006
     as opposed to floating
        in the capsule?

09:02.042 --> 09:03.975
             TONY:
        Well, I suppose
     there was a difference

09:04.010 --> 09:05.176
     psychologically, sir.

09:05.212 --> 09:07.511
Inside the capsule,
you have a feeling of security,

09:07.547 --> 09:10.381
and outside, you wonder
whether you're gonna float away.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.685
I must say it was...
an exhilarating feeling.

09:14.721 --> 09:15.720
         It must have been.

09:15.755 --> 09:18.022
       I really envy you, major.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.992
   I can arrange for you to go
 along on one of our moon shots.

09:21.027 --> 09:22.927
    That's very kind of you,
            general,

09:22.963 --> 09:24.929
     but I'm really swamped
     with work right here.

09:24.965 --> 09:27.098
       Well, if you gentlemen
    will come back to my office,

09:27.133 --> 09:29.167
           I'll show you the new
             correlation charts

09:29.202 --> 09:31.736
      we have on the moon probe.

09:31.771 --> 09:34.605
           All right. All right.

09:34.640 --> 09:36.241
       Oh, Major Nelson.

09:36.276 --> 09:37.775
Yes, sir.

09:37.810 --> 09:38.977
                  How's Tiger?

09:39.012 --> 09:40.144
    Tiger?

09:40.180 --> 09:41.479
Oh, uh, fine.
 Just fine.

09:41.514 --> 09:44.215
        Say hello to him for me,
               won't you?

09:44.251 --> 09:45.416
    Yes.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.831
    [CLEARS THROAT]

10:00.867 --> 10:04.168
Your, uh, dinner is ready,
         master.

10:04.204 --> 10:05.569
                 [CHUCKLES]

10:05.605 --> 10:07.571
         Okay, I'll-- I'll be
      with you in just a minute.

10:07.607 --> 10:09.240
               Soon as I finish
             these correlations.

10:11.811 --> 10:14.679
     Well, how about that.

10:14.714 --> 10:16.848
              Say, what are you
             all dressed up for?

10:16.883 --> 10:18.516
    I thought we were eating
            at home.

10:18.551 --> 10:19.851
          Oh, yes.

10:19.886 --> 10:22.553
But I thought it might be nice
    if we dressed for it.

10:22.588 --> 10:25.924
Ah, you look handsome,
       master.

10:25.959 --> 10:26.925
                Thanks.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.192
Oh, you would look wonderful

10:28.228 --> 10:29.727
on the deck of your own yacht.

10:29.762 --> 10:32.097
     Jeannie, we've been through
              all this.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.365
              No yacht.

10:34.400 --> 10:36.467
 I don't know how I'm gonna make
         you understand.

10:36.502 --> 10:38.136
    I don't want anything else
           in the world

10:38.171 --> 10:39.270
   except to be an astronaut.

10:39.305 --> 10:41.239
               Now why don't you
                just forget it,

10:41.274 --> 10:43.241
          and we'll go down
     and enjoy your dinner. Hmm?

10:43.276 --> 10:45.076
  If you say so, master.

10:45.111 --> 10:46.110
             That's what I wish.

10:46.146 --> 10:47.711
 Oh, you should see
what I made for you.

10:47.747 --> 10:48.712
I have a wonderful--

10:48.748 --> 10:49.713
         No, now, don't tell me.

10:49.749 --> 10:50.781
     I want it to be a surprise.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.050
        All right.

10:52.085 --> 10:54.785
 I can't get over that.
You just look wonderful.

10:56.889 --> 10:57.956
        [DOORBELL RINGS]

10:57.991 --> 10:58.990
It's probably Roger.

10:59.025 --> 11:00.325
He's crazy about your cooking.

11:00.360 --> 11:01.960
        Uh--

11:02.695 --> 11:03.661
Oh, Dr. Bellows.

11:03.696 --> 11:04.829
                   Major.

11:07.233 --> 11:10.701
   This is, uh-- Uh,
an unexpected pleasure.

11:10.736 --> 11:12.003
                   Is it?
        Yes.

11:12.038 --> 11:13.804
             Were you going out?
Going out, sir?

11:13.840 --> 11:15.873
No, I was just having
a little dinner here alone.

11:15.908 --> 11:18.843
             In a dinner jacket?
A dinner jacket?

11:18.878 --> 11:20.845
  Oh. Ha, ha.

11:20.880 --> 11:22.480
Uh, well, it's an old habit.

11:22.515 --> 11:24.282
  It, uh-- It makes
the food taste better.

11:24.317 --> 11:25.383
                      Oh.

11:29.722 --> 11:31.155
               Uh, are you going
                somewhere, sir?

11:31.191 --> 11:32.490
Yes, you might say that.

11:32.525 --> 11:35.360
 I'm taking a trip
that's long overdue.

11:35.395 --> 11:36.560
                  Good, good.

11:36.596 --> 11:39.263
                I-- I mean,
          have a good time, sir.

11:39.299 --> 11:40.664
               Drop me a line
            if you get a chance.

11:40.700 --> 11:43.001
I expect to have the most
interesting time of my life.

11:43.036 --> 11:44.035
                     Good.

11:44.070 --> 11:45.436
                Uh, may I ask
             where you're going?

11:45.472 --> 11:47.338
Indeed you may, major.

11:47.374 --> 11:51.042
              Oh.

11:51.077 --> 11:54.111
                Did you say
          you were dining alone?

11:54.146 --> 11:56.046
   The table is set for two.

11:56.082 --> 11:57.381
              Two?

11:57.416 --> 11:59.049
            Oh, oh,

11:59.085 --> 12:01.619
      you never know when
 a friend will drop in, do you?

12:03.322 --> 12:05.389
Well, thanks for dropping in
    to say goodbye, sir.

12:05.424 --> 12:08.126
              Oh. I haven't come
                to say goodbye.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.527
    You haven't?

12:09.562 --> 12:10.695
           No, major.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.229
      As a matter of fact,
         you might say

12:12.265 --> 12:13.631
  that I've come to say hello.

12:14.600 --> 12:17.368
         I'm moving in with you.

12:23.176 --> 12:25.076
     This is really
a bachelor's place, sir.

12:25.111 --> 12:27.078
I don't know how comfortable
      I can make you.

12:27.113 --> 12:28.646
     Oh, the couch will be fine.

12:28.681 --> 12:30.048
             I'm not here
          to be comfortable.

12:31.651 --> 12:34.018
Well, why are you here, sir?

12:34.054 --> 12:37.655
       Because General Peterson
      thinks I'm losing my mind.

12:37.690 --> 12:40.358
      But I'm gonna prove to him
           that I'm normal.

12:43.496 --> 12:46.531
               Uh, shall we, uh,
                go in to dinner?

12:49.035 --> 12:50.068
                  Ahh!

12:52.906 --> 12:55.073
   Is that pheasant under glass?

12:55.108 --> 12:56.140
                       Probably.

12:57.176 --> 12:58.476
           Truffles?

13:00.613 --> 13:05.516
                Rack of lamb?
             Stuffed artichokes?

13:05.551 --> 13:06.650
    Who cooked this, major?

13:06.685 --> 13:08.752
        Oh, uh, we have
  a frozen-food market just--

13:08.788 --> 13:10.388
          [LOUD CRASH]

13:12.258 --> 13:14.892
      It's my housekeeper.

13:14.928 --> 13:16.060
               Ah.

13:16.096 --> 13:17.361
    You have a housekeeper?

13:17.396 --> 13:20.264
     Well, you don't think
      that I cooked this.

13:20.299 --> 13:21.999
       Oh, well, no, sir.

13:22.034 --> 13:23.334
                     No, no, no.

13:23.369 --> 13:25.436
 Patricia is a marvelous cook.

13:26.773 --> 13:29.207
Uh, but she doesn't like anyone
      in her kitchen, sir.

13:29.242 --> 13:30.274
Patricia is very, uh--

13:31.243 --> 13:34.111
                   Patricia,
               your housekeeper?

13:34.146 --> 13:37.314
      Pedro, my houseboy.

13:37.349 --> 13:38.716
              Pedro...

13:39.752 --> 13:41.685
this is Doctor Bellows.

13:41.720 --> 13:43.921
   [SQUEAKY SPANISH ACCENT]
    Hello, Doctor Bellows.

13:43.957 --> 13:45.089
                 Hello, Pedro.

13:45.124 --> 13:47.624
        I was just complimenting
              Major Nelson

13:47.660 --> 13:50.694
                on how marvelous
                 the food looks.

13:50.729 --> 13:54.832
 Yes, uh, well, uh, I think we
 ought to go in and eat, sir--

13:54.867 --> 13:57.568
             Uh, tell me,
      where are you from, Pedro?

13:57.603 --> 14:00.138
      I was born in Paris.

14:00.173 --> 14:01.940
                     Paris?

14:01.975 --> 14:03.474
              <i> Sí.</i>

14:03.509 --> 14:06.744
           That's why
     I'm so very good cook.

14:06.779 --> 14:09.047
Yeah, we really ought
to start eating, sir.

14:09.082 --> 14:12.049
    Uh, how long have you worked
          for Major Nelson?

14:12.084 --> 14:13.451
     Uh, he just started--
 One year.

14:13.486 --> 14:15.486
  He just started a year ago.

14:15.522 --> 14:16.921
I-- I think we ought to eat now.

14:16.956 --> 14:18.489
         <i> Ai Chihuahua.</i>

14:18.525 --> 14:20.057
  Is he gonna stay for dinner?

14:20.092 --> 14:22.059
   Uh, Pedro,

14:22.094 --> 14:23.961
he's not only staying
     for dinner.

14:23.996 --> 14:25.797
He's moved in with me.

14:25.832 --> 14:27.231
       [DISHES SMASHING]

14:27.266 --> 14:29.033
             Pedro.

14:31.537 --> 14:34.405
            Now, Pedro. Pedro.

14:36.376 --> 14:37.875
             Uh, I-- I told you,

14:37.910 --> 14:39.943
      Pedro doesn't like anybody
         in his kitchen, sir.

14:39.979 --> 14:43.080
He may be a marvelous cook,
major, but he's dangerous.

14:43.115 --> 14:45.450
       I'd get rid of him
         if I were you.

14:45.485 --> 14:48.052
        Believe me, sir.
 You've no idea how I've tried.

14:48.087 --> 14:50.154
      [DISHES SHATTERING]

14:52.124 --> 14:53.090
       [DOORBELL RINGING]

14:53.125 --> 14:55.292
    Coming, coming, coming.

14:59.632 --> 15:01.131
                       Tony.

15:01.167 --> 15:03.501
         Is-- Is anything wrong?

15:03.536 --> 15:06.771
I just acquired
a permanent houseguest.

15:06.806 --> 15:08.038
Three guesses.

15:08.074 --> 15:09.206
                  Suzanne?

15:09.242 --> 15:11.509
Doctor Alfred Bellows.

15:11.544 --> 15:13.578
         Oh. Oh, you're kidding.

15:13.613 --> 15:14.579
What are we going to do?

15:14.614 --> 15:15.713
        What are <i> we</i> going to do?

15:15.749 --> 15:17.314
               What are you--
           It's your houseguest.

15:17.350 --> 15:19.216
          How did he happen to
       move in with you, anyway?

15:19.252 --> 15:20.685
Well, he didn't happen
to move in.

15:20.720 --> 15:22.286
He moved in because
he's suspicious.

15:22.321 --> 15:26.858
  Oh, there's nothing worse than
    a suspicious head shrinker.

15:26.893 --> 15:28.559
       I need your help.

15:28.594 --> 15:30.127
         Wait a minute,
     don't give him to me.

15:30.162 --> 15:32.230
    I'm not giving you him.
    I'm giving you Jeannie.

15:32.265 --> 15:33.731
            You are?

15:33.766 --> 15:35.733
         Oh. Oh, well,
      I'll drink to that.

15:37.237 --> 15:39.303
    Uh, just until I get rid
        of Dr. Bellows.

15:39.338 --> 15:41.338
Remember, it's only
for the duration.

15:41.374 --> 15:43.441
Oh, what do you think I am?

15:43.476 --> 15:46.444
        I know what you are.
    I'm taking a chance, anyway.

15:47.880 --> 15:51.048
           [SNORING]

16:16.075 --> 16:17.308
             Fire.

16:20.580 --> 16:21.579
             Fire!

16:24.150 --> 16:25.182
Fire.

16:25.551 --> 16:26.917
Fire.

16:28.154 --> 16:29.753
         Fire!

17:12.865 --> 17:14.531
            [SMASH]

17:14.567 --> 17:16.098
I got it. I got it.

17:16.135 --> 17:17.768
    What's going on?

17:17.803 --> 17:19.170
                I don't know,
             but whatever it is,

17:19.204 --> 17:20.871
            I think we've gotten
            to the bottom of it.

17:20.906 --> 17:21.872
            It was a bottle.

17:21.906 --> 17:23.240
      A bottle?
What kind of a bottle?

17:23.275 --> 17:24.508
  I trailed the bottle over--

17:32.151 --> 17:34.618
                     Oh.

17:40.727 --> 17:43.927
    Well, it's not a total loss.

17:43.963 --> 17:46.330
  You better get some rest, sir.

17:46.366 --> 17:47.598
I don't understand it.

17:47.633 --> 17:49.567
    I-- I must have
    had a nightmare.

17:49.602 --> 17:50.835
    It was so real.

17:50.870 --> 17:52.135
                    Yes.
            These things happen.

17:52.171 --> 17:54.938
Yes. I'll-- I'll buy
you a new lamp, of course.

17:54.974 --> 17:58.409
             Oh, no. You don't
            have to bother, sir.

17:58.444 --> 18:00.944
              It was an antique.

18:02.147 --> 18:05.449
           Sir, uh, could we get
              some sleep now?

18:05.485 --> 18:08.318
               I have an awful
             rough day tomorrow.

18:08.354 --> 18:12.155
Oh, yes, yes, of course.
I'm-- I'm terribly sorry.

18:12.191 --> 18:13.657
    I-- Oh.

18:13.693 --> 18:16.694
My nerves seem to be on edge.
                     Yeah.

18:16.729 --> 18:18.696
        Oh.

18:18.731 --> 18:23.634
  When I was a...
   A small boy,

18:23.669 --> 18:25.269
 my mother loved
my younger brother

18:25.304 --> 18:26.804
more than she loved me. I--

18:26.839 --> 18:28.873
I didn't think I minded it
       at the time,

18:28.908 --> 18:32.376
but then as years went by,
  I began to resent it.

18:32.411 --> 18:35.112
I didn't actually hate
     my brother,

18:35.147 --> 18:40.484
but I found myself working out
  ways to do away with him.

18:44.323 --> 18:48.292
        [FOOT DRAGGING]

18:59.272 --> 19:00.271
        [DRAGGING STOPS]

19:06.446 --> 19:08.679
           [GRUMBLES]

19:11.317 --> 19:14.184
      [DRAGGING CONTINUES]

19:14.219 --> 19:16.186
        [DRAGGING STOPS]

19:25.831 --> 19:30.701
        [TRAIN CHUGGING]

19:48.687 --> 19:54.524
       [HEAVY BREATHING]

20:37.236 --> 20:39.003
           [GRUMBLES]

20:41.207 --> 20:43.774
         [LION ROARING]

20:58.691 --> 21:02.626
    [HIGH-PITCHED WHISTLING]

21:41.300 --> 21:44.668
    [NATIVE AMERICAN DRUMS,
           WHOOPING]

21:46.372 --> 21:47.404
           [SCREAMS]

21:47.439 --> 21:50.741
      [WHOOPING CONTINUES]

22:03.489 --> 22:04.521
    What is it? What is it?

22:04.556 --> 22:05.823
The Indians.
                     Huh?

22:05.858 --> 22:07.491
Indians are coming.
                  Indians?

22:07.526 --> 22:09.927
Listen, they're closing in.

22:09.962 --> 22:11.896
      Doctor, you've got to pull
          yourself together.

22:11.931 --> 22:13.130
I am together.

22:13.166 --> 22:15.900
I heard these footsteps.
Then this train was coming.

22:15.935 --> 22:17.501
Then someone was
breathing in my ear.

22:17.536 --> 22:18.903
Then this lion roared.

22:18.938 --> 22:20.570
                    Lion roared?
    Yes.

22:20.606 --> 22:22.472
That was just before
the bomb start falling.

22:22.508 --> 22:23.573
       The bomb started falling?

22:23.609 --> 22:24.574
       Yes.
    And then--

22:24.610 --> 22:26.944
Ooh, then the tom-toms started.

22:26.979 --> 22:28.913
They were on the warpath.

22:28.948 --> 22:31.215
Yelling and screaming.
 It was a nightmare.

22:31.250 --> 22:33.517
    Yeah, doctor, that's exactly
      what it was: a nightmare.

22:33.552 --> 22:35.152
   Now, you must get some sleep.

22:35.188 --> 22:36.553
    Sleep?

22:39.358 --> 22:41.891
 I wouldn't sleep in this house
again if my life depended on it.

22:41.927 --> 22:43.327
    You wouldn't?

22:43.362 --> 22:45.795
    If you'll take my advice,
you'll get out of here yourself.

22:45.831 --> 22:47.764
              In my opinion,
          this house is haunted.

22:47.799 --> 22:49.666
Oh, you don't believe
in ghosts, do you, sir?

22:49.701 --> 22:51.935
       Well, I didn't yesterday,
            but I do today.

22:53.772 --> 22:55.739
Well, doctor, aren't you
   gonna get dressed?

22:55.774 --> 22:56.940
        There's no time.

22:56.976 --> 22:58.942
     They may be gathering
      for another attack.

23:02.815 --> 23:03.780
           [CHUCKLES]

23:03.816 --> 23:04.781
            Well...

23:04.817 --> 23:08.385
            [LAUGHS]

23:10.189 --> 23:11.555
    He's gone, master.

23:11.591 --> 23:12.990
                    Yes, I know.

23:13.025 --> 23:15.292
                  Oh, Jeannie.

23:15.327 --> 23:17.060
               You're marvelous.

23:17.096 --> 23:19.463
      I can't tell you how great
       it is to be alone again.

23:29.842 --> 23:32.543
             ROGER:
         Good morning.

23:32.578 --> 23:33.544
                     Hi, Roge.

23:33.579 --> 23:34.812
Good morning,
Major Healey.

23:34.847 --> 23:35.880
      Just call me master.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.347
Master?

23:37.383 --> 23:38.949
       Well, temporarily,
           of course.

23:38.985 --> 23:41.051
   Well, look, since I'll be
    taking over for a while,

23:41.086 --> 23:44.021
  I made out a little list of
 some of the things I'll need--

23:44.056 --> 23:46.390
             Roger, there's been
              a change in plans,
                for one thing.

23:46.425 --> 23:48.291
         First of all,
  I'd like some ski equipment,

23:48.327 --> 23:50.394
       nothing elaborate.
       About 15 outfits.

23:50.429 --> 23:51.595
        And I'd like--

23:51.631 --> 23:53.363
             Jeannie won't be
         staying with you, Roge.

23:53.399 --> 23:55.633
Maybe someplace in the mountains
      with about 30 rooms,

23:55.668 --> 23:56.767
       with a cute maid.

23:56.802 --> 23:58.201
                 Roger, uh,
            I'm keeping Jeannie.

23:58.236 --> 23:59.669
             What?

23:59.705 --> 24:00.804
      I'm keeping Jeannie.

24:00.840 --> 24:02.839
      Doctor Bellows left.
    Everything is all right.

24:02.875 --> 24:04.608
        What do you mean
    everything's all right?

24:04.643 --> 24:05.943
 I just lost a 30-room chalet,

24:05.978 --> 24:09.312
     a 15-piece ski outfit
        and a cute maid.

24:09.348 --> 24:10.647
           All right.

24:10.683 --> 24:13.049
     Uh, Jeannie, could you
       give him the maid?

24:13.085 --> 24:14.851
      Certainly, master.

24:14.887 --> 24:18.555
    You mean you're gonna--
        Oh, what a pal.

24:18.590 --> 24:20.157
     I'm Agnes.

24:20.192 --> 24:22.993
I don't work on Sundays,
and I take holidays off.

24:23.029 --> 24:24.528
I don't do no heavy cleanin'.

24:24.564 --> 24:25.729
And I cook only twice a week.

24:25.765 --> 24:27.731
    Now, the food's simple,
    so if you like it fancy,

24:27.766 --> 24:29.165
        you can just go
        to a restaurant.

24:29.201 --> 24:31.201
         Besides that,
  I want two television sets.

24:31.236 --> 24:33.436
      One for the bedroom
    and one for the kitchen.

24:33.472 --> 24:36.940
             [♪♪♪]

24:40.479 --> 24:44.581
             [♪♪♪]
